  "notes": "Bosnian (bosanski) — Shtokavian standard of the Serbo-Croatian pluricentric language, written in Gaj's Latin alphabet (30 letters, including the digraphs dž, lj, nj which are single letters). Highly phonemic: one letter = one phoneme. ⟨r⟩ may be syllabic between consonants. Bosnian retains /h/ in more positions than the Croatian and Serbian standards. Pitch accent and vowel length are phonemic but not written.",
